Agent name: Growth OpportunitiesTool name: customer_modules  Issue: Growth Opportunities agent does not invoke the 'customer_modules' tool when running. This causes issues with the growth opportunities recommendations as the missing context causes the LLM to recommend existing modules as upsells, because they do not appear under the account's existing modules.Evidence:Call id: 7685125162766707276First run UUID: 80613c4f-4fce-446d-b0d4-7207db08af59timestamp: 21 Aug 2025, 17:15:31[missing tool data in the prompt. should appear after the ‘Customer modules’ title, similar to the ‘Available modules’ data]The tool grid shows that in this tool was only invoked once during this time and under the above UUID:[the tool was invoked only by the ‘Risk analysis’ agent who also uses this tool and is located above the ‘Growth opps’ agent in the config file]The tool returned data in the first invocation by the ‘Risk analysis’ agent:{
	"http_status_code": "200",
	"response": {
		"message": "Success",
		"body": "Compensation, Sandbox, Talent Package, Core"
	}
}Upon discovering this, I deleted the agent’s folder from the cache folder under the call ID in AWS and ran the process again for this call. Second run UUID: 312b1f30-4783-4af4-96cb-5a1a736ffd01Timestamp: 02 Sep 2025, 15:24:09This time, the tool was invoked by the agent:The tool data appeared in the agent’s input prompt:The agent provided relevant upsell opportunities.

